main event: The report documents several UFO sightings in the Cleveland, Ohio area in 1964.
interesting points: One sighting involved an object that was circular in shape and giving off a bright, pulsating light. It quickly accelerated and moved out of sight.
Another sighting described an object that was cigar-shaped, approximately 30 feet long and 10 feet wide, metallic in color, and moved at a high rate of speed before making a sharp right angle turn.
A third sighting was of a bright, white light that appeared larger than a star, remained stationary for about 15 minutes, then moved off at a high rate of speed.
The reports indicate that these sightings were made by mature, reliable observers, including someone associated with a known military activity.
The Air Force's Project Blue Book program investigated these sightings, but concluded there was 'insufficient data for evaluation' in most cases due to lack of details.
sighted object: circular, cigar-shaped, and bright white light objects
witnesses: civilian observers, including someone associated with military activity
